entry.title: Run GetPlatformTimeZone on worker thread to avoid jank on Windows
entry.content:
On Windows, the Timezone changes are detected by listening to

WM_TIMECHANGE event. Whenever the time change event (WM_TIMECHANGE) is

received, a call is made to windows API ::GetTimeZoneInformation to get

the current time zone. If the current time zone differs from the

previously cached time zone, then the notification is sent to the

observers of TimeZoneMonitor.



::GetTimeZoneInformation which is called from within GetPlatformTimeZone

method is causing jank in Browser Process Main UI thread (blocking

BrowserProcess UI thread on an avg for ~1.5 seconds).



The fix here is to execute GetPlatformTimeZone as a task on worker

thread instead on UI thread. The time zone value (returned from this

worker thread task) is passed to another task which resumes execution

on the UI thread to notify time zone change to the observers of

TimeZoneMonitor if the recent and previous time zone are different.

entry.title: utr: Fix arg parsing for multiple tests & add unittests
entry.content:
As-is, the arg parser treats all consecutive non-named args after

"--test" to put into the "test" named arg. This has some incorrect

behavior when it comes last before the mode. eg:

"./tools/utr --force -B try -b linux-rel -t url_unittests test"



That command fails with:

"No suites on the bot matched the request for test"



So this fixes that by changing the "-t" arg from accepting N vals

after it, to only accepting one, but allowing "-t" to be repeated.

This fixes the above error.



And also add unittest coverage to enforce that.

entry.title: [UNO] Move password to account store after promo sign in
entry.content:
This CL implements the functionality to move the password to the

account store after a successful sign in event from the password sign in promo.



- If the user is already signed in on the web, the password is moved

immediately after the sign in.

- If the user does not have an account yet, the

`AutofillSigninPromoTabHelper` will listen for sign in events

with the correct access point for 50 minutes and move the password

once this there was a sign in.

- If the account is in a "sign in paused" state (e.g. signed into

Chrome, signed out from the web), the password will be uploaded to

the account store directly after successful verification and does not

need to be moved (addressed in b:329811644).

entry.title: [flex] Sync ContentBlockSizeFunc with BlockNode::ComputeMinMaxSizes
entry.content:
Previously when computing the flex base size we'd explicitly handle

transferred sizes. There isn't a need to do this, instead we can

rely on determining the content-size (for both axes).



The primary logic change is to harmonize ContentBlockSizeFunc with how

content sizes work in BlockNode::ComputeMinMaxSizes.



If we have an aspect-ratio - try and resolve our inline-size, and if

definite use that as the content size.



Otherwise use the intrinsic size - clamped by the transferred min/max

sizes.



This patch allows us to remove a bunch of indirect dependencies on

InlineLengthUnresolvable/BlockLengthUnresolvable.

entry.title: [WebAuthn] Minor refactor of UserVerifyingKey's Windows implementation
entry.content:
Changes:

1. I've verified that the Windows async calls do keep references to the

`IAsyncOperations` so we don't need to keep ComPtrs around until the

`PostAsyncHandler` callbacks are invoked, so those are removed.

2. Avoid caching the key generation and signing callbacks in

`UserVerifyingKeyProviderWin` and `UserVerifyingSigningKeyWin`.

Instead we use `base::SplitOnceCallback` (via a helper that splits a

callback into three)

3. Use `base::BindPostTaskToCurrentDefault` to remove some of the manual

callback wrapping that was being done before.

4. Due to (2) above, `EnclaveManager` no longer has to be diligent about

ensuring the key provider stays alive, so I've eliminated the caching

there.

5. Make error reporting more consistent.

in the facilitated payments manager, which contains the cross platform
